\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The ontological sextet is specialised into several foundational ontologies, e.g., UFO [@Guizzardi:2015ky], GFO [@Herre2010], SUMO [@Niles:2001], YAMAYATO [@Mizoguchi:2010vv], BFO [@Grenon2004], DOLCE [@Masolo2002] and more, with their similarities and differences [@Jansen2008]. They all assume a certain philosophical viewpoint to accurately describe categories that exist in reality. We consider this the *philosophical cornerstone* that produces semantics that are faithful to reality. Following our statement that every modelling language carries an ontological commitment, it then remains the responsibility of the (domain) analyst to select the viewpoint that is most appropriate for its purpose, in order to select the modelling language that describes the types of things that exist in the domain of application the most accurate.}
